        "setup": "In [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/), select or create a project, enable the [Chrome Management API](https://developers.google.com/chrome/management/guides/setup), then configure the OAuth consent screen and create an `OAuth 2.0 Client ID` under [APIs & Services > Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials). Use the client to obtain Google OAuth access tokens for the Chrome Management API; the setup guide also points to [OAuth Playground](https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/) for testing.",
